            		<note>The following seven labels are engraved in archaic Tamil and Grantha characters on a group of rocks, one of which, on account of a natural cavity in it, is locally known as 'Noṇḍi Vīrappaṉ Kudiraitoṭṭi'. The names Kevadaperundachchaṉ and Kollaṉ Śēmagaṉ found in this place indicate that the persons bearing these names belonged to the artisan class. One of the labels also gives the name Guṇamallaḥ. On account of their palaeographical interest, these labels, as also the one given in the previous inscription <supplied reason="explanation">SII 12.23 = IP ***<!--update!--></supplied>, are included here and some of them are reproduced on plate VI <supplied reason="explanation">plate II in fact</supplied>.</note>
